# Abo Shalbak — Environment profiles
#
# Use TWO separate files (never one shared .env for both):
#
#   .env.development  →  your PC, npm start (ports 5000/3001/3002)
#   .env.store        →  live shop, npm run store:up / Docker (port 3000)
#
# See docs/DEV_VS_STORE.md

## Development — copy to .env.development

```env
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=5000
HOST=127.0.0.1

JWT_SECRET=dev-only-jwt-secret-not-for-production-use
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=8h

DATABASE_PATH=./data/supermarket.db
BACKUP_DIR=./backups

# Keep Telegram empty in dev
TELEGRAM_USE_POLLING=0
TELEGRAM_REFUND_BOT_TOKEN=
TELEGRAM_EXPIRY_BOT_TOKEN=
TELEGRAM_REFUND_CHAT_ID=
TELEGRAM_EXPIRY_CHAT_ID=
```

Start: `npm start` from repo root.

## Store (Docker) — copy to .env.store

```env
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=3000
HOST=0.0.0.0

JWT_SECRET=your-long-random-secret-here
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=8h

DATABASE_PATH=/app/data/supermarket.db
BACKUP_DIR=/app/backups

TELEGRAM_USE_POLLING=1
TELEGRAM_REFUND_BOT_TOKEN=
TELEGRAM_EXPIRY_BOT_TOKEN=
TELEGRAM_REFUND_CHAT_ID=
TELEGRAM_EXPIRY_CHAT_ID=
```

Start: `npm run store:up`

Store URLs: `http://YOUR_LAN_IP:3000/pos` and `/admin`

Templates: `.env.development.example` and `.env.store.example`

For remote admin via Tailscale, see DEPLOY-TAILSCALE.md.
